s of fragmentation trees and\ncoalescents appearing in the recent literature. Our results are also suggestive\nof new models and tools, for applications in Bayesian Nonparametrics/Machine\nLearning, where PD(\\alpha,\\theta) bridges are often referred to as Pitman-Yor\nprocesses.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Aug 2013 19:45:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 1 Sep 2013 07:16:51 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 6 Sep 2013 04:49:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-09-09"}
